Common.PostalAddresses.Common.Line1: ±52,300 SF Aircraft Maintenance and Painting Facility

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Fort Worth Spinks Airport, just 14 miles from Fort Worth, Texas.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The facility was built in 2007 and has been used as
an aircraft paint and interior operation. There are
three hangar bays inside the facility providing
multiple options for operations on site, as well as
office and shop space.

The property is well-suited for a variety of operations,
including maintenance, repair, overhaul, parts, and
painting for a variety of aircraft ranging from
helicopters to large aircraft.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: ±52,300 SF AIRCRAFT MAINTENANCE AND PAINTING FACILITY

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE, as exclusive advisor, is pleased to present to qualified investors a unique opportunity to acquire San Antonio Express-News Building located at 301 Avenue E in downtown San Antonio, Texas. The eight-story, 303,023 SF iconic building is exceptionally well-located fronting Avenue E, 3rd Street and N Alamo Street. The immediate area is surrounded by offices, hotels, major tourist attractions such as The Alamo, the world-famous River Walk and Pearl District.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Iconic Building on Major, ±2.13 Acre Full City Block in Downtown San Antonio
